<h4>Magician Class Issues</h4>



<p>The last thing I want this site to be is another place to rant and

rave.&nbsp; However, there are a few things about all classes that just don't

make much sense.&nbsp; The magician class is no exception.&nbsp; Here, I list a

few of what I feel are the more important class issues.&nbsp; If you'd like to

comment or add to the list, <a href="mailto:nenelar@hotmail.com">please feel

free to email me</a>.</p>



<p>Right now, I feel that the magician class is quite viable as-is, even though 

we are no longer one of the top solo classes in the game.</p>



<h3>AAXP</h3>



<p>Our Class level AAXP simply has no stand-out winners.</p>

<div align="center">

  <center>

  <table border="1">

    <tr>

      <td><b>MGB</b></td>

      <td>Magicians get only a damage shield that can be cast on others.&nbsp;

        Here's why a magician will never use MGB:

        <ol>

          <li>Aegis of Ro lasts 13 minutes, the MGB ability resets every 72

            minutes</li>

          <li>There just isn't the need to DS everyone</li>

        </ol>

      </td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><b>Frenzied Burnout</b></td>

      <td>It's broke!&nbsp; Here are the problems with it:

        <ol>

          <li>Flurries are not landing enough as the pet swings and misses like a 4-year old playing t-ball</li>

          <li>Rampage isn't effective since the pet is almost never fighting more than 1 unmez'd mob at a time</li>

          <li>Net issue -- it doesn't do sufficient damage -- for the 

          investment, this needs to have a higher DPS or needs to be on a much shorter timer</li>

        </ol>

      </td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><b>Host of Elements</b></td>

      <td>This is a great AA ... with only 1 change needed.&nbsp; The pets push 

      enough that with walls being a problem, a game coding issue becomes a mage 

      class issue.&nbsp; If HoE pets did not push (I don't even know if this is 

      configurable in VI's design) this would not be an issue.</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><b>Quick Summoning</b></td>

      <td>A great AA, but with the 50% haste cap, QS3 is not worth the investment.</td>

    </tr>

  </table>

  </center>

</div>

  <h3>&nbsp;</h3>

<h3>Pets</h3>

  <p>Recent improvements to our pets have been welcome.&nbsp; There are

  remaining issues, however:</p>

<div align="center">

  <center>

  <table border="1">

    <tr>

      <td><b>Epic DS</b></td>

      <td>The epic pet is still slow in buffing itself.&nbsp; I have waited more

        than 10 minutes as recently as 10/11/2002 for the epic to cast it's

        AuraofElementalMastery.</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><b>Fire Elemental</b></td>

      <td>This pet still needs work:<ol>

        <li>A pet should never attempt to cancel a magic buff unless VI is 

        willing to allow the pet to intelligently cancel magic.&nbsp; Having a 

        pet that randomly cancels a dire charm or a slow on a mob is a good way 

        to end up needing a res.</li>

        <li>Kindle isn't going to cut it.&nbsp; This pet needs a bigger mana 

        pool...likely by a factor of 2.</li>

        <li>Let mages see pet spell damage (and melee damage while we're at it) 

        on its own filter.</li>

      </ol>

      </td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><b>Haste Cap</b></td>

      <td>Pets seem to be haste capped at a delay of 19.&nbsp; Mages

        have been given spells and skills that exceed the cap <i>by design</i>.&nbsp;

        Why is the cap in place?&nbsp; Examples that exceed the cap include:

        <ol>

          <li>Ancient: Burnout - 80%</li>

          <li>Frenzied Burnout - 99%</li>

          <li>Burnout III (60%) and the Muzzle of Mardu (10%) - 70%</li>

          <li>Burnout IV (65%) and the Muzzle of Mardu (10%) - 75%</li>

        </ol>

        <p class="warn">This seems to have been addressed for 61+ pets.&nbsp; As 
        VI fixed this by making haste scale &quot;in line with the mage's level&quot; I am 
        uncertain as to how lower level mages (lower level pets) are effected.</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><b>Monster Summoning</b></td>

      <td>With the change that made all elementals non-aggro, summoned monsters

        lost one of the their primary benefits.&nbsp; With the change that made

        most elementals better at melee, summoned monsters lost another

        benefit.&nbsp; Ultimately, there is little reason to use a monster other

        than for the entertainment value.</td>

    </tr>

  </table>

  </center>

</div>

<h3>

&nbsp;</h3>

<h3>

Spells</h3>

<div align="center">

  <center>

  <table border="1">

    <tr>

      <td><b>Elemental Silence</b></td>

      <td>The level limit of this spell should be higher.&nbsp; As is stands, 

      the spell's limit of 60 prohibits its use in all but BOT (unless high 

      level mages feel like fighting in lower level zones like The Hole).</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><b>PBAoE</b></td>

      <td><p><i>Pre LDoN Issue: Scintillation is underpowered compared to the wizard
        equivalent.&nbsp; It's only about half as effective -- and has not been
        upgraded since Kunark.&nbsp; Level 65 magicians have only a 607 damage <u>level 51</u> spell!</i></p><p>The LDoN answer 
		to this issue, 
		Wind of the Desert is absolutely horrid.&nbsp; 780 mana for 1050 damage every 8.5 seconds?&nbsp; It's a worse 
		sustained DPS than Scintillation.</p></td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><b>Rain AE</b></td>

      <td>Magician rains at high levels aren't well thought out.&nbsp; Two of

        the spells are actually near duplicates:

        <ol>

          <li><u>Manastorm</u> costs 427 mana for 675 damage and 50 mana at

            level 59.</li>

          <li><u>Maelstrom of Electricity</u> costs 475 mana for 675 damage at

            level 60.</li>

        </ol>

        <p>Why does MoE cost more mana for less overall damage (no mana drain)

        at a higher level than Manastorm?</td>

    </tr>

    </table>

  </center>

